description.narrative: As per administrative data, in 2019 antenatal care coverage and skilled birth attendance remained high at 93% and 92% respectively, with 89% of primary care facilities providing the five Basic Emergency Obstetric and New born care (BEmONC) signal functions. UNICEF continued to support issues of quality of care, employing more effective capacity building measures such as clinical mentorship and maternal and perinatal death surveillance and response which have played a critical role in obtained results. Integrated outreach in districts with low performing Reproductive Maternal New born Child Adolescent Health indicators has also been important to address inequities in service coverage. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
